<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->
<h3 id="13-drop-the-logo">13. Drop the Logo</h3>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Unbranded pieces tend to have a higher more luxe feel to them because it leaves a sense of mystery. All of a sudden, people are no longer going to judge you on the price of the garment but more so on how it looks, how it feels, and how it fits.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>I don’t like wearing brands because it leaves a mystery. Instead of judging me on the brand, you judge me on the fit of the clothing, how it looks on me, how it fits, and how it feels.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->
<h3 id="14-take-risks-by-trying-new-attires">14. Take Risks by Trying New Attires</h3>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>I’m sure you heard of this saying, “high risk, high reward.” Of course, you’re going to have some misses when you step outside your comfort zone trying something new. This is still the best way to cultivate your style, so you don’t look so robotic and like everybody else.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>This is why if you’re a guy, that maybe never worn a polo shirt or a button-down, and you feel like that’s outside your comfort zone, take a risk, try it once and see how it makes you think, and see how people compliment you or look at you or treat you differently. On the other hand, if your guy the only where’s Jordan, reduce doing that. Step out of that and try something different.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Try a clean white leather sneaker or try a loafer—something that’s outside your norm, that will develop your style.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->
<h3 id="15-keep-your-glasses-in-your-front-pocket">15. Keep Your Glasses in Your Front Pocket</h3>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":8474} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image"><img src="https://gentlemendistrict.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/Keep-Your-Glasses-in-Your-Front-Pocket-.jpg.webp" alt="Keep Your Glasses in Your Front Pocket" class="wp-image-8474"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>When you aren’t using your pair of sunglasses to shield your eyes and making you look sexy, please and please again, don’t put them on your head or your neck or behind your head—that just looks tacky.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Taking a look at the stylish men of&nbsp;<a href="https://www.pittimmagine.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Pitti Uomo</a>, the only elegant way to carry your frames when you’re not wearing them is on your chest pocket—this is subtlety at its best. This style of hack move is vital.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->
<h3 id="16-mix-your-sport-and-your-smart-clothes">16. Mix your sport and your smart clothes</h3>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Whether that’s wearing sweats with your regular button-up, or a hoodie under a suit, or an overcoat, the lines of men are becoming more and more blurred, meaning that everything goes. We call this ‘hi-low dressing.’</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>When you learn to execute this correctly, the beauty of it is that now you can step outside your comfort zone and wear things that most of the time would seem stuffy. Still, in reality, you’re going to be comfortable in looking style.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->
